{
  "analysis": "The naive attack is still running and is too slow. It should be stopped and replaced with a reverse round-by-round solver. However Panel 2's proposed layered code still has bugs in both ciphertext inversion and pre-mix check, so I will write a corrected version. The encryption output is merge(right, left) after post-mix, so ciphertext high = right4, low = left4 ^ right4. Thus r4 = ct_hi, l4 = ct_low ^ ct_hi. Reversing round j sets r_{j} = l_{j+1}, l_{j} = r_{j+1} ^ F(r_j ^ rk_j). After reversing round 0, l0/r0 are the post-premix values, and plaintext halves are pl=l0, pr=r0^l0.",
  "plan": "Stop the running process. Write a corrected attack.c with 2^20 outer loop over k3, storing state before round 3, then inner 2^20 loops for k2, k1, k0 with early rejection against plaintext. Compile and run it. Once it prints the four seeds, use decrypt to create plaintexts.txt and verify it matches pairs for known pairs.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "C-c",
      "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "cat > /app/attack.c <<'EOF'
#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdint.h>
#include <stdlib.h>

static inline uint32_t expand(uint32_t key) {
    key &= 0xFFFFF;
    return key ^ (key << 16) ^ (key * 12345u);
}

static inline uint8_t g_function(uint8_t a, uint8_t b, uint8_t x) {
    uint8_t temp = (a + b + x) & 0xFF;
    return ((temp << 2) | (temp >> 6)) & 0xFF;
}

static inline uint32_t f_function(uint32_t input_val) {
    uint8_t x[4], y[4];
    for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) { x[i] = input_val & 0xFF; input_val >>= 8; }
    y[2] = g_function(x[3] ^ x[2], x[1] ^ x[0], 1);
    y[3] = g_function(x[3], y[2], 0);
    y[1] = g_function(x[1] ^ x[0], y[2], 0);
    y[0] = g_function(x[0], y[1], 1);
    uint32_t output = 0;
    for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) output |= (uint32_t)y[i] << (8 * i);
    return output;
}

#define N 32
static uint64_t pt[N], ct[N];

int main(void) {
    FILE *fp = fopen("/app/pairs.txt", "r");
    if (!fp) { perror("pairs"); return 1; }
    int n = 0;
    while (n < N && fscanf(fp, "%lu %lu", &pt[n], &ct[n]) == 2) n++;
    fclose(fp);
    if (n < N) { fprintf(stderr, "Only %d pairs\n", n); return 1; }

    uint32_t pl[N], pr[N];
    for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
        pl[i] = (uint32_t)(pt[i] >> 32);
        pr[i] = (uint32_t)pt[i];
    }

    for (uint32_t k3 = 0; k3 < (1u<<20); k3++) {
        uint32_t rk3 = expand(k3);
        uint32_t a3[N][2];
        for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
            uint32_t hi = (uint32_t)(ct[i] >> 32);
            uint32_t lo = (uint32_t)ct[i];
            uint32_t r4 = hi;
            uint32_t l4 = lo ^ hi;
            uint32_t r3 = l4;
            uint32_t l3 = r4 ^ f_function(r3 ^ rk3);
            a3[i][0] = l3; a3[i][1] = r3;
        }
        for (uint32_t k2 = 0; k2 < (1u<<20); k2++) {
            uint32_t rk2 = expand(k2);
            uint32_t a2[N][2];
            for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
                uint32_t r2 = a3[i][1];
                uint32_t l2 = a3[i][0] ^ f_function(r2 ^ rk2);
                a2[i][0] = l2; a2[i][1] = r2;
            }
            for (uint32_t k1 = 0; k1 < (1u<<20); k1++) {
                uint32_t rk1 = expand(k1);
                uint32_t a1[N][2];
                for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
                    uint32_t r1 = a2[i][1];
                    uint32_t l1 = a2[i][0] ^ f_function(r1 ^ rk1);
                    a1[i][0] = l1; a1[i][1] = r1;
                }
                for (uint32_t k0 = 0; k0 < (1u<<20); k0++) {
                    uint32_t rk0 = expand(k0);
                    int ok = 1;
                    for (int i = 0; i < N && ok; i++) {
                        uint32_t r0 = a1[i][1];
                        uint32_t l0 = a1[i][0] ^ f_function(r0 ^ rk0);
                        if (l0 != pl[i] || (r0 ^ l0) != pr[i]) ok = 0;
                    }
                    if (ok) {
                        printf("%u %u %u %u\n", k0, k1, k2, k3);
                        return 0;
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    }
    fprintf(stderr, "no key found\n");
    return 1;
}
EOF
